      <item>
        <title>Support for React-quill node package</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[cristianbote]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Hey <a class="mention" href="https://community.frontity.org/u/tix">@tix</a> I’ve updated my comment and the linked codesandbox after you’ve already seen it, I believe. Both methods work, but with <code>loadable</code> you don’t have to do the <code>useEffect</code> and <code>useState</code> ‘dance’.</p>
<p>Regarding lazy loading via dynamic imports, it’s really when you see those kind of errors that <code>document</code> or <code>window</code> is undefined when this is the case. Also as a rule of best practices when you have a large package it’s always better to split the logic between pages, in order for those pages that are not using it to not have to load unnecessary scripts.</p>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/support-for-react-quill-node-package/3907/11">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
